
[1]hepar

   HE'PAR, n. [L. hepar,the liver.] A combination of sulphur with an
   alkali was formerly called by chimists hepar sulphuris, liver of
   sulphur, from its brown red color. The term has been applied to all
   combinations of alkali or earth with sulphur or phosphorus.

   The hepars are by modern chimists called sulphurets.
